# The Teken library itself
#
# Teken is 256-colour capable as standard.
# Conventional FreeBSD keyboard maps do distinguish return key from enter/send key.
# It overlays its own F1 to F12 on top of the SCO console defaults for function keys, which are retained for F13 upwards, but which make this record too long for termcap to handle.
# The home and end keys generate ECMA-48 sequences per the SCO vt system, rather than DEC VT sequences like the Linux vt system.
# The DEC VT input sequences are find and select keys, as DEC intended.
# Teken supports C25CURS, which has more than 2 states, so we use it in preferene to DECSM/DECRM 25.
#
