# nosh virtual terminal in FreeBSD console mode
#
# We substitute HPR, VPR, HPB, and VPB for the counted motions, because these have strict zero-is-zero semantics.
# An application that explicity asks to move zero characters in any direction will get what it asked for.
#
# Scrolling regions are available, with DECSTBM; as is adjusting tabstops with HTS, CTC, and TBC.
# An alternate screen buffer is available.
#
teken-256color|teken-16color|FreeBSD console:\
	:co#80:li#25:it#8:rs=\E[!p:\
	:bl@:\
	:DO=\E[%de:LE=\E[%dj:RI=\E[%da:UP=\E[%dk:\
	:cs=\E[%i%d;%dr:\
	:te=\E[?1049l:ti=\E[?1049h:\
	:st=\EH:ct=\E[3g:\
	:tc=teken-lib:

